page.title: 20SURVEYING AROUND KEELBY
page.content: On Wednesday 19th of June a group of us set off in Mrs Stowe's car out of Keelby towards Grimsby.We stopped in a layby where there was a caravan.The fields around us were used for crops. We were in square eleven on the map. We turned left at Riby crossroads,the fields were still used for crops.At Oak Holt we found a packing station hidden by trees. We turned right at the first junction and had a walk.We found a nest hidden in a hedge.The fields towards Healing Wells were used for crops.At Healing Wells we found a farm where we turned round to come back. At Riby crossroads we saw a surveyor who was planing out a new crossroads because the old one was too dangerous. On the way back we saw alsorts of birds.We had covered most of square eleven and some of ten and twelve.
